headline: Sherwin-Williams Q4 Earnings Call Highlights
summary: Sherwin-Williams (NYSE:SHW) executives told investors the company finished 2025 with a “strong” fourth quarter despite a demand environment that management repeatedly described as “softer for longer,” and provided initial guidance calling for low- to mid-single-digit sales growth and higher earnings

headline: SHW Q4 Deep Dive: Stable Margins Amid Choppy End Markets and Realistic 2026 Outlook
summary: Paint and coating manufacturer Sherwin-Williams (NYSE:SHW) announced better-than-expected revenue in Q4 CY2025, with sales up 5.6% year on year to $5.60 billion. Its non-GAAP profit of $2.23 per share was 3.1% above analysts’ consensus estimates.
